'I stayed there for 3 nights while attending a conference. The room was OK but breakfast was not included in the price - and we had to pay £17.50 for a very ordinary buffet breakfast which frankly was not very nice at all. Lots of things ran out, both the tea and the coffee were stewed beyond the point of no return, and the cooked breakfast was greasy and pretty awful. This was a two star breakfast for £17.50! The internet access was £12.50 a day - and we had been led to believe it would be included in the fairly hefty room charge. There were various other little irritations and overall this hotel is a bit of a rip off. Room Tip: Find somewhere local to get a nice breakfast not l See more room tips'